Phillips has already given at least one fan theory some validity. In an interview with the&nbsp;Los Angeles Times, he stoked buzz on one claim that suggests Phoenix&rsquo;s Arthur Fleck is the first Joker and not necessarily the villain that will eventually face off against Bruce Wayne/Batman. The theory states Arthur is the original Joker whose actions in the film&rsquo;s climax go on to inspire the Batman-hating Joker (perhaps that Joker was a member of the film&rsquo;s violent protest).<br />
<br />
&ldquo;Maybe Joaquin&rsquo;s character&nbsp;inspired&nbsp;the Joker,&rdquo; Phillips told the Times. &ldquo;You don&rsquo;t really know. His last line in the movie is. &lsquo;You wouldn&rsquo;t get it.&rsquo; There&rsquo;s a lot going on in there that&rsquo;s interesting.&rdquo;

